                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Μελάνιππος">Μελάνιππος</name> 
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Κάλλιππος" type="patronymic">Καλλίππω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Mélanippos fils de Kallippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Melanippos son of Kallippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Melanippos figlio di Kallippos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This man might be the son of Kallippos son of Melanippos who is the first <foreign rend="italic">strategos</foreign> on duty in 320 (see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr010800</ref>, l. 74). 
                    About that family, see <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>102, 117</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
